quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  45,22,"God created the heavens and earth for a true purpose: to reward each soul according to its deeds. They will not be wronged"
  45,23,"[Prophet], consider the one who has taken his own desire as a god, whom God allows to stray in the face of knowledge, sealing his ears and heart and covering his eyes- who can guide such a person after God [has done this]? Will you [people] not take heed"
  45,24,"They say, ‘There is only our life in this world: we die, we live, nothing but time destroys us.’ They have no knowledge of this; they only follow guesswork. Their only argument"
  45,25,"when Our clear revelations are recited to them, is to say, ‘Bring back our forefathers if what you say is true.’"
  45,26,"[Prophet], say, ‘It is God who gives you life, then causes you to die, and then He gathers you all to the Day of Resurrection of which there is no doubt, though most people do not comprehend.’"